Use the standard library
This is how to flip_case of string:
   Remember that result is ""
   Remember that n is string's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that c is item i in string
      Remember that nc is c
      When c is at least 65, then:
         When c is at most 90, then:
            Remember that nc is sum of c and 32
         End when
      End when
      When c is at least 97, then:
         When c is at most 122, then:
            Remember that nc is diff of c and 32
         End when
      End when
      Add result to nc
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> flip_case of "Hello"
"hELLO"
>>> flip_case of ""
""
>>> flip_case of "Hello!"
"hELLO!"